# WireGuard Portal (wg-portal) on EC2 with Keycloak OIDC

> This doc is generated with the help of AI but verified by me from real debugging experience. No fluff.

---

## Overview

This guide covers deploying wg-portal v2 on an AWS EC2 instance with Keycloak as the OIDC authentication provider. wg-portal is a web UI for managing WireGuard VPN peers and configs.

> ℹ️ **Memory**: wg-portal runs fine under 2 GB. A `t3.small` is sufficient.

---

## Architecture

```
Internet
    |
    ├── :51820/udp ──► [ WireGuard tunnel ]
    |
    └── :8888/tcp ───► [ wg-portal web UI ]
                            |
                            | OIDC auth (server-to-server)
                            | :80 via private IP
                            v
                       [ Keycloak EC2 ]
```

Two separate EC2 instances — one for wg-portal/WireGuard, one for Keycloak. They communicate over the VPC private network for server-side OIDC token exchange. The browser communicates with Keycloak via the public IP for the login redirect.

