## Critical Config Values

| Field | Value | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `web.external_url` | Public IP of WireGuard EC2 | Browser follows the OIDC callback redirect to this URL |
| `auth.oidc.base_url` | **Must match Keycloak's issuer exactly** | wg-portal fetches the OIDC discovery doc from this URL and validates that the `issuer` field in the response matches it. Private IP vs public IP mismatch = startup failure |

> ⚠️ **The `base_url` must match `KC_HOSTNAME` set on Keycloak.** If Keycloak has `KC_HOSTNAME: 3.6.93.195`, then `base_url` must be `http://3.6.93.195/realms/<realm>` — not the private IP, even though both are in the same VPC.

