## EC2 Security Group

The WireGuard EC2 needs its **own security group** — and that security group must actually be **attached to the instance**. Defining a security group in Terraform but not including it in `vpc_security_group_ids` means none of its rules apply.

```hcl
resource "aws_instance" "wireguard" {
  vpc_security_group_ids = [
    aws_security_group.wireguard.id,    # <-- must include this
    aws_security_group.private_ssh.id,
  ]
}
```

Required inbound rules:

| Type | Protocol | Port | Source | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Custom UDP | UDP | 51820 | 0.0.0.0/0 | WireGuard tunnel traffic |
| Custom TCP | TCP | 8888 | Your IP only | wg-portal web UI |
| SSH | TCP | 22 | Your IP only | Admin access |

