## IP Address Reference

This is the most confusing part of this setup — different components need different IPs for different reasons:

| Config | IP to use | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `web.external_url` | WireGuard EC2 **public IP** | Browser hits this after OIDC callback |
| `auth.oidc.base_url` | Keycloak EC2 **public IP** | Must match Keycloak's `KC_HOSTNAME` / issuer |
| Keycloak redirect URI (in Keycloak admin) | WireGuard EC2 **public IP** | Browser is redirected here after login |
| Keycloak web origins (in Keycloak admin) | WireGuard EC2 **public IP** | Browser makes CORS requests here |

> ℹ️ Even though both EC2s are in the same VPC, `base_url` must use the **public IP** if `KC_HOSTNAME` is set to the public IP on Keycloak. The issuer in the OIDC discovery doc must match `base_url` exactly — mixing public/private IPs causes wg-portal to fail at startup.

