## Startup and Access

```bash
# Start wg-portal
docker compose up -d

# Check logs — look for "successfully setup all external auth providers"
docker logs -f wg-portal
```

**Healthy startup looks like:**
```
Configuration loaded!
interface state restored
Application startup complete
started web service address=:8888
successfully setup all external auth providers   # <-- this line confirms Keycloak OIDC is working
```

**Access:** `http://<wireguard-ec2-public-ip>:8888`

You should see a login page with a **"Login with Keycloak"** button.

